</emphasis>
Frons lacking interfrontal setulae; ocellar setae very weak or absent; proclinate orbital setae shorter than reclinate ones; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[623,647,1447,1461]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[724,732,1447,1461]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">1</subScript>
distally somewhat divergent; epandrium and surstylus entirely fused (
<figureCitation box="[227,326,1470,1495]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1840,1863]" captionTargetBox="[282,1313,1175,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-506@2.[276,1318,1166,1812]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2. Luzonimyia hirsutina sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Syntergosternite 7+8 (syntgst 7+8), epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); B. surstylus (inner view); C. sixth sternite (6th st), hypandrium (hypd), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); D. ditto (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929148/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[338,376,1470,1495]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1634,1657]" captionTargetBox="[344,1242,1062,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-459@3.[340,1248,1058,1613]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3. Luzonimyia stictogaster sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); B. cerci (posterior view); C. hypandrium, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (lateral view); D. ditto (ventral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929154/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">3A</figureCitation>
); paramere absent (
<figureCitation box="[595,727,1470,1495]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="2.[151,263,1840,1863]" captionTargetBox="[282,1313,1175,1805]" captionTargetId="figure-506@2.[276,1318,1166,1812]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2. Luzonimyia hirsutina sp. nov., male terminalia: A. Syntergosternite 7+8 (syntgst 7+8), epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); B. surstylus (inner view); C. sixth sternite (6th st), hypandrium (hypd), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); D. ditto (lateral view). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4929148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4929148/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="295">Figs. 2C, D</figureCitation>
